ray.rml

Interface Angle

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Addable<Angle>, java.lang.Comparable<Angle>, Divisible<Angle>, Multiplicable<Angle>, Negatable<Angle>, Subtractable<Angle>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Degreef, Radianf

    public interface Angle
extends Addable<Angle>, Subtractable<Angle>, Multiplicable<Angle>, Divisible<Angle>, java.lang.Comparable<Angle>, Negatable<Angle>
    An angle is the figure formed by two rays sharing the same vertex end point and represents a measurement of the amount of rotation between them.
    Author:
    Raymond L. Rivera
